main event: On December 6, 1958, multiple unidentified flying objects (UFOs) were observed over Washington, D.C. by reliable witnesses, including Air Force personnel.
interesting points: The objects were tracked on radar indicating they could perform maneuvers suggesting intelligent control., Witnesses reported seeing bright, circular objects emitting a glow., The objects were estimated to be between 20-30 feet in diameter., The sightings included multiple accounts from military personnel., The incident remains classified as 'unresolved' due to insufficient explanation for the observed phenomena.
witness description: reliable witnesses including U.S. Air Force personnel
